cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimization problems related to matroids, which are a fundamental concept in combinatorial optimization and graph theory. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as matroids are often used in game theory to model strategic interactions between players. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the optimization problems and provides algorithms for some cases. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as matroids are a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as matroids have applications in coding theory and information theory.
